                                              "styleGuidelines":  "## Brand \u0026 Style\nThis design system embodies a **Corporate Modern** aesthetic with a strong emphasis on **Glassmorphism** and soft, layered depth. It is tailored for high-performance mobile interfaces—specifically SaaS, health, or productivity tools—that require a balance of professional reliability and contemporary lightness.\n\nThe personality is clean, systematic, and fluid. The interface uses translucent surfaces, background blurs, and vibrant blue accents to create a sense of clarity and forward momentum. Visual hierarchy is established through \"soft-tactile\" elements: subtle gradients, high-quality blurs, and precise elevation that make the UI feel responsive and premium.\n\n## Layout \u0026 Spacing\nThe layout follows a **fluid grid** model optimized for mobile viewports (390px width as the baseline).\n\n- **Rhythm:** Spacing is built on a 4px base unit. \n- **Margins:** Standard screen margins are set to 16px. Vertical sections are separated by 20px to allow the content to breathe.\n- **Touch Targets:** A strict minimum of 44px is maintained for all interactive elements to ensure accessibility.\n- **Reflow:** On wider screens, card containers should cap their width or expand into multi-column layouts, maintaining the 12px internal gap.\n\n## Elevation \u0026 Depth\nDepth is created through a combination of **Glassmorphism** and **Ambient Shadows**.\n\n- **Glass Effects:** Interactive containers use a background blur (18px to 24px) combined with a semi-transparent white fill and a 0.5px \"glass stroke\" to simulate a physical edge.\n- **Shadows:** Shadows are highly diffused and tinted with the primary blue color (`rgba(31, 67, 126, 0.08)`) rather than using neutral grays. This keeps the interface feeling \"lit\" from within.\n- **Floating Action Buttons (FAB):** Use a high-intensity shadow and a subtle inner-stroke highlight to sit at the highest z-index.\n\n## Components\n- **Buttons:** Primary buttons feature a diagonal blue gradient and 16px rounding. Secondary buttons should use `surface-soft` or `surface-glass` with `primary` text.\n- **Cards:** The core of the UI. Cards must use the `card` elevation and `surface` glass fill. Internal padding is strictly 16px.\n- **Icons:** Use rounded, outline-style icons with a consistent 1.8px stroke width. Inactive states use a muted slate-blue, while active states use the primary brand blue.\n- **Chips/Badges:** Use the `status` typography and `pill` rounding. Backgrounds should be `primary-subtle` or semantic `soft` variants (e.g., `success-soft`).\n- **Inputs:** Fields should be styled with `surface-soft`, using a 12px radius and a subtle `border` stroke that strengthens to `primary` on focus.",
